idered Steinbeck's masterpiece. In the first 75 years since it was published, it sold 14 million copies.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Grapes_of_Wrath_10_facts_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Steinbeck#cite_note-Grapes_of_Wrath_10_facts-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>The winner of the 1962 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Literature\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Literature\">Nobel Prize in Literature<\/a>, he has been called \"a giant of American letters\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Why_do_children_study_Of_Mice_and_Men.3F_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Steinbeck#cite_note-Why_do_children_study_Of_Mice_and_Men.3F-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> His works are widely read abroad and many of his works are considered classics of Western literature.<\/p><p>Most of Steinbeck's work is set in southern and central California, particularly in the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Salinas_Valley\" title=\"Salinas Valley\">Salinas Valley<\/a> and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/California_Coast_Ranges\" title=\"California Coast Ranges\">California Coast Ranges<\/a> region. His works frequently explored the themes of fate and injustice, especially as applied to downtrodden or <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Everyman\" title=\"Everyman\">everyman<\/a> protagonists.<\/p>","name":"John Steinbeck","place_of_birth":"Salinas Valley, California, USA","place_of_death":"New York, New York, USA","text":"John Steinbeck , Literature, 1962","year":1962.0}